Researchers in England and Wales found a strong link between schizophrenia and the age of fathers, with mutations in sperm contributing to the risk.
France, Britain, and the Czech Republic have high cannabis consumption rates, prompting a 10-million euro campaign in France to highlight its harmful effects.
Genetic research in Iceland revealed a region on the 17th chromosome linked to schizophrenia.
In the US, a study showed that early marijuana use increased the risk of psychosis.
Scientists are now working on creating a detailed model of the human brain's neocortex to better understand brain function and disorders.
